@startuml
title Recovery flow (in-game CPU reset)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 40

participant "PC\n(host side)" as S
participant "CPU\n(custom)" as C

== During the match (just before CPU's turn) ==
S -> C : MOd5
note right : opponent's move\n(PC retains it as "the most recent instruction")
... CPU computing move ...

== Unexpected reset ==
note over C #FFEBEE
  Power glitch / watchdog /
  manual reset, etc.
  CPU enters BOOT state
end note

== Reboot, unsolicited send ==
C -> S : RE
note left : READY\nboot complete; re-send request

== PC-side recovery ==
note over S
  Re-send the most recent instruction
  (SB / MOd? / BO... etc.) to restore the position
end note
S -> C : MOd5
note right : re-send the previous MOVE

== Match resumes ==
C -> S : MOd7
note left : CPU's move (after recovery)
... back to the normal loop ...

@enduml
